Conditional Statements:
To make the set instructions execute only when the given condition is True.
Used to decide whether the code has to be executed or skip based on the given condition.
Block of code : set of instructions.
         It will execute only when the given condition is true. 
If:-if the condition is true it will executed.
If-else
Else if
Switch
Ternary Operator
Example1:
let a=10
       let b=4
       if(a<b){
        document.write("Hello Malli....")
       }
       else{
        document.write("Hello Yaswanth....")
       }
Output:
Hello Yaswanth…
Example2:
let a=10
       let b=4
       let c=3
       if(a<b){
        document.write("Hello Malli....")
       }
       else if(a>b || b>c){
        document.write("Hello CSE")
       }

       else{
        document.write("Hello Yaswanth....")
       }
Output:
Hello CSE
Example3:
let a=prompt("Enter Your Age:")
       let name=prompt("Enter Your name:")
       if(a<18){
        document.write(`${name} You are not aligible..`)
       }else{
        document.write(`${name} You are aligible...`)
       }
Output:


Yaswanth You are aligible... 
Example4:
let a=prompt("Enter person1 Score:")
       let b=prompt("Enter person2 Score")
       let sum=a+b
       if((a>300 || b>300) && sum>500){
        document.write("We are aligible for the team up")
       }else{
        document.write("We are not aligible to team up")
       }

Output:
a=400
b=200
We are aligible for the team up.       
